<table width="100%" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" border="0"><tr><td bgcolor="#0d0f14" height="6" style="font-size:1px;line-height:1px;">&nbsp;</td></tr></table>
<table width="100%" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" border="0">
  <tr>
    <td bgcolor="#0a1520" style="padding:5px 12px;font-family:Courier New,monospace;font-size:8pt;color:#5a7a8a;letter-spacing:1px;">
      72-HOUR OUTLOOK · TO 07 MARCH 2026
    </td>
  </tr>
</table>
<table width="100%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="0" border="0" bgcolor="#1e2d3d">
  <tr><td bgcolor="#1a2d3a" style="padding:6px 8px;font-family:Courier New,monospace;font-size:8pt;color:#00d4ff;font-weight:bold;white-space:nowrap;"><b>SCENARIO</b></td><td bgcolor="#1a2d3a" style="padding:6px 8px;font-family:Courier New,monospace;font-size:8pt;color:#00d4ff;font-weight:bold;white-space:nowrap;"><b>PROBABILITY</b></td><td bgcolor="#1a2d3a" style="padding:6px 8px;font-family:Courier New,monospace;font-size:8pt;color:#00d4ff;font-weight:bold;white-space:nowrap;"><b>PRINCIPAL INDICATOR</b></td><td bgcolor="#1a2d3a" style="padding:6px 8px;font-family:Courier New,monospace;font-size:8pt;color:#00d4ff;font-weight:bold;white-space:nowrap;"><b>ASSESSMENT</b></td></tr>
  <tr><td bgcolor="#141820" style="padding:5px 8px;font-family:Trebuchet MS,Arial,sans-serif;font-size:9pt;color:#dde6f0;vertical-align:top;">Israeli counter-strike on IRGC missile infrastructure inside Iran</td><td bgcolor="#141820" style="padding:5px 8px;font-family:Trebuchet MS,Arial,sans-serif;font-size:9pt;color:#dde6f0;vertical-align:top;">40–55%</td><td bgcolor="#141820" style="padding:5px 8px;font-family:Trebuchet MS,Arial,sans-serif;font-size:9pt;color:#dde6f0;vertical-align:top;">Israeli cabinet breaks strategic ambiguity; US green-light signals</td><td bgcolor="#141820" style="padding:5px 8px;font-family:Trebuchet MS,Arial,sans-serif;font-size:9pt;color:#dde6f0;vertical-align:top;">The penetration rate from the Haifa salvo has materially increased the pressure to act. A strike within 72 hours would be premature by historical Israeli patterns, but not outside precedent.</td></tr>
<tr><td bgcolor="#111620" style="padding:5px 8px;font-family:Trebuchet MS,Arial,sans-serif;font-size:9pt;color:#dde6f0;vertical-align:top;">Continuation of current exchange rhythm — salvo and counter-intercept — without escalation to strikes on Iranian territory</td><td bgcolor="#111620" style="padding:5px 8px;font-family:Trebuchet MS,Arial,sans-serif;font-size:9pt;color:#dde6f0;vertical-align:top;">35–45%</td><td bgcolor="#111620" style="padding:5px 8px;font-family:Trebuchet MS,Arial,sans-serif;font-size:9pt;color:#dde6f0;vertical-align:top;">No Israeli cabinet announcement; IRGC does not repeat salvo size</td><td bgcolor="#111620" style="padding:5px 8px;font-family:Trebuchet MS,Arial,sans-serif;font-size:9pt;color:#dde6f0;vertical-align:top;">The most likely path if both sides are managing the pace of escalation. Houthi maritime operations continue regardless.</td></tr>
<tr><td bgcolor="#141820" style="padding:5px 8px;font-family:Trebuchet MS,Arial,sans-serif;font-size:9pt;color:#dde6f0;vertical-align:top;">Iranian attempt to close or restrict Hormuz passage in response to Israeli or US military action</td><td bgcolor="#141820" style="padding:5px 8px;font-family:Trebuchet MS,Arial,sans-serif;font-size:9pt;color:#dde6f0;vertical-align:top;">10–20%</td><td bgcolor="#141820" style="padding:5px 8px;font-family:Trebuchet MS,Arial,sans-serif;font-size:9pt;color:#dde6f0;vertical-align:top;">Trigger: Israeli or US strike inside Iranian territory</td><td bgcolor="#141820" style="padding:5px 8px;font-family:Trebuchet MS,Arial,sans-serif;font-size:9pt;color:#dde6f0;vertical-align:top;">Iran has historically treated Hormuz closure as an extreme measure with severe economic self-harm. It remains a genuine option under sufficient pressure. Probability rises sharply if strikes occur.</td></tr>

</table>
<table width="100%" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" border="0"><tr><td bgcolor="#0d0f14" height="6" style="font-size:1px;line-height:1px;">&nbsp;</td></tr></table>
<table width="100%" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" border="0"><tr><td bgcolor="#0d0f14" height="8" style="font-size:1px;line-height:1px;">&nbsp;</td></tr></table>
<table width="100%" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" border="0">
  <tr>
    <td bgcolor="#0d0f14" style="padding:4px 12px 8px 12px;">
      <span style="font-family:Courier New,monospace;font-size:10pt;color:#00d4ff;font-weight:bold;letter-spacing:2px;">
        <b>WARNING INDICATORS</b>
      </span>
    </td>
  </tr>
</table>
<table width="100%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="0" border="0" bgcolor="#1e2d3d">
  <tr>
    <td bgcolor="#1a4a5a" style="padding:6px 8px;font-family:Courier New,monospace;font-size:8pt;color:#00d4ff;font-weight:bold;width:55px;"><b>ID</b></td>
    <td bgcolor="#1a4a5a" style="padding:6px 8px;font-family:Courier New,monospace;font-size:8pt;color:#00d4ff;font-weight:bold;width:40px;"><b>DOM</b></td>
    <td bgcolor="#1a4a5a" style="padding:6px 8px;font-family:Courier New,monospace;font-size:8pt;color:#00d4ff;font-weight:bold;"><b>INDICATOR</b></td>
    <td bgcolor="#1a4a5a" style="padding:6px 8px;font-family:Courier New,monospace;font-size:8pt;color:#00d4ff;font-weight:bold;width:110px;"><b>STATUS</b></td>
    <td bgcolor="#1a4a5a" style="padding:6px 8px;font-family:Courier New,monospace;font-size:8pt;color:#00d4ff;font-weight:bold;width:80px;"><b>CHANGE</b></td>
    <td bgcolor="#1a4a5a" style="padding:6px 8px;font-family:Courier New,monospace;font-size:8pt;color:#00d4ff;font-weight:bold;width:200px;"><b>DETAIL</b></td>
  </tr>

  <tr><td bgcolor="#141820" style="padding:6px 8px;font-family:Courier New,monospace;font-size:8pt;color:#00d4ff;"><b>WI-01</b></td><td bgcolor="#141820" style="padding:6px 8px;font-family:Courier New,monospace;font-size:8pt;color:#5a7a8a;">D1</td><td bgcolor="#141820" style="padding:6px 8px;font-family:Trebuchet MS,Arial,sans-serif;font-size:9pt;color:#dde6f0;">Israeli security cabinet formally authorises strikes on Iranian territory</td><td bgcolor="#141820" style="padding:6px 8px;font-family:Courier New,monospace;font-size:8pt;color:#d68910;font-weight:bold;"><b>WATCHING</b></td><td bgcolor="#141820" style="padding:6px 8px;font-family:Courier New,monospace;font-size:8pt;color:#d68910;">ELEVATED</td><td bgcolor="#141820" style="padding:6px 8px;font-family:Trebuchet MS,Arial,sans-serif;font-size:8pt;color:#5a7a8a;font-style:italic;">Cabinet using 'evaluating options' language. Pressure increasing after Haifa penetrations.</td></tr>

  <tr><td bgcolor="#111620" style="padding:6px 8px;font-family:Courier New,monospace;font-size:8pt;color:#00d4ff;"><b>WI-02</b></td><td bgcolor="#111620" style="padding:6px 8px;font-family:Courier New,monospace;font-size:8pt;color:#5a7a8a;">D2</td><td bgcolor="#111620" style="padding:6px 8px;font-family:Trebuchet MS,Arial,sans-serif;font-size:9pt;color:#dde6f0;">Iran restores IAEA access to Fordow</td><td bgcolor="#111620" style="padding:6px 8px;font-family:Courier New,monospace;font-size:8pt;color:#5a7a8a;font-weight:bold;"><b>NOT TRIGGERED</b></td><td bgcolor="#111620" style="padding:6px 8px;font-family:Courier New,monospace;font-size:8pt;color:#d68910;">NEW (inverted tripwire)</td><td bgcolor="#111620" style="padding:6px 8px;font-family:Trebuchet MS,Arial,sans-serif;font-size:8pt;color:#5a7a8a;font-style:italic;">Restoration would signal diplomatic off-ramp. Absence sustains escalatory pressure.</td></tr>

  <tr><td bgcolor="#141820" style="padding:6px 8px;font-family:Courier New,monospace;font-size:8pt;color:#00d4ff;"><b>WI-03</b></td><td bgcolor="#141820" style="padding:6px 8px;font-family:Courier New,monospace;font-size:8pt;color:#5a7a8a;">D3</td><td bgcolor="#141820" style="padding:6px 8px;font-family:Trebuchet MS,Arial,sans-serif;font-size:9pt;color:#dde6f0;">IRGC Navy physically impedes commercial traffic in Strait of Hormuz</td><td bgcolor="#141820" style="padding:6px 8px;font-family:Courier New,monospace;font-size:8pt;color:#d68910;font-weight:bold;"><b>WATCHING</b></td><td bgcolor="#141820" style="padding:6px 8px;font-family:Courier New,monospace;font-size:8pt;color:#d68910;">ELEVATED</td><td bgcolor="#141820" style="padding:6px 8px;font-family:Trebuchet MS,Arial,sans-serif;font-size:8pt;color:#5a7a8a;font-style:italic;">Patrol activity up; no interdiction yet. Probability rises materially on Israeli/US strikes.</td></tr>

  <tr><td bgcolor="#111620" style="padding:6px 8px;font-family:Courier New,monospace;font-size:8pt;color:#00d4ff;"><b>WI-04</b></td><td bgcolor="#111620" style="padding:6px 8px;font-family:Courier New,monospace;font-size:8pt;color:#5a7a8a;">D4</td><td bgcolor="#111620" style="padding:6px 8px;font-family:Trebuchet MS,Arial,sans-serif;font-size:9pt;color:#dde6f0;">US confirms B-52H weapons manifest includes Massive Ordnance Penetrator</td><td bgcolor="#111620" style="padding:6px 8px;font-family:Courier New,monospace;font-size:8pt;color:#d68910;font-weight:bold;"><b>WATCHING</b></td><td bgcolor="#111620" style="padding:6px 8px;font-family:Courier New,monospace;font-size:8pt;color:#d68910;">NEW</td><td bgcolor="#111620" style="padding:6px 8px;font-family:Trebuchet MS,Arial,sans-serif;font-size:8pt;color:#5a7a8a;font-style:italic;">Confirmation would shift Diego Garcia deployment from signalling to preparation.</td></tr>

  <tr><td bgcolor="#141820" style="padding:6px 8px;font-family:Courier New,monospace;font-size:8pt;color:#00d4ff;"><b>WI-05</b></td><td bgcolor="#141820" style="padding:6px 8px;font-family:Courier New,monospace;font-size:8pt;color:#5a7a8a;">D5</td><td bgcolor="#141820" style="padding:6px 8px;font-family:Trebuchet MS,Arial,sans-serif;font-size:9pt;color:#dde6f0;">CISA elevates critical infrastructure alert to Emergency Directive</td><td bgcolor="#141820" style="padding:6px 8px;font-family:Courier New,monospace;font-size:8pt;color:#d68910;font-weight:bold;"><b>WATCHING</b></td><td bgcolor="#141820" style="padding:6px 8px;font-family:Courier New,monospace;font-size:8pt;color:#d68910;">NEW</td><td bgcolor="#141820" style="padding:6px 8px;font-family:Trebuchet MS,Arial,sans-serif;font-size:8pt;color:#5a7a8a;font-style:italic;">Current advisory (AA26-063A) is non-binding. Emergency Directive would indicate active compromise of US systems.</td></tr>

  <tr><td bgcolor="#111620" style="padding:6px 8px;font-family:Courier New,monospace;font-size:8pt;color:#00d4ff;"><b>WI-06</b></td><td bgcolor="#111620" style="padding:6px 8px;font-family:Courier New,monospace;font-size:8pt;color:#5a7a8a;">D5</td><td bgcolor="#111620" style="padding:6px 8px;font-family:Trebuchet MS,Arial,sans-serif;font-size:9pt;color:#dde6f0;">Iran internet connectivity drops below 30% (full blackout threshold)</td><td bgcolor="#111620" style="padding:6px 8px;font-family:Courier New,monospace;font-size:8pt;color:#d68910;font-weight:bold;"><b>WATCHING</b></td><td bgcolor="#111620" style="padding:6px 8px;font-family:Courier New,monospace;font-size:8pt;color:#d68910;">ELEVATED</td><td bgcolor="#111620" style="padding:6px 8px;font-family:Trebuchet MS,Arial,sans-serif;font-size:8pt;color:#5a7a8a;font-style:italic;">Currently at 61%. Full blackout historically precedes or accompanies significant domestic events.</td></tr>

</table>

<table width="100%" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" border="0"><tr><td bgcolor="#0d0f14" height="8" style="font-size:1px;line-height:1px;">&nbsp;</td></tr></table>
<table width="100%" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" border="0">
  <tr>
    <td bgcolor="#0d0f14" style="padding:4px 12px 8px 12px;">
      <span style="font-family:Courier New,monospace;font-size:10pt;color:#00d4ff;font-weight:bold;letter-spacing:2px;">
        <b>COLLECTION GAPS</b>
      </span>
    </td>
  </tr>
</table>
<table width="100%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="0" border="0" bgcolor="#1e2d3d">
  <tr>
    <td bgcolor="#1a4a5a" style="padding:6px 8px;font-family:Courier New,monospace;font-size:8pt;color:#00d4ff;font-weight:bold;width:55px;"><b>ID</b></td>
    <td bgcolor="#1a4a5a" style="padding:6px 8px;font-family:Courier New,monospace;font-size:8pt;color:#00d4ff;font-weight:bold;width:40px;"><b>DOM</b></td>
    <td bgcolor="#1a4a5a" style="padding:6px 8px;font-family:Courier New,monospace;font-size:8pt;color:#00d4ff;font-weight:bold;width:70px;"><b>SEVERITY</b></td>
    <td bgcolor="#1a4a5a" style="padding:6px 8px;font-family:Courier New,monospace;font-size:8pt;color:#00d4ff;font-weight:bold;"><b>GAP</b></td>
    <td bgcolor="#1a4a5a" style="padding:6px 8px;font-family:Courier New,monospace;font-size:8pt;color:#00d4ff;font-weight:bold;"><b>SIGNIFICANCE</b></td>
  </tr>

  <tr><td bgcolor="#141820" style="padding:6px 8px;font-family:Courier New,monospace;font-size:8pt;color:#00d4ff;"><b>CG-01</b></td><td bgcolor="#141820" style="padding:6px 8px;font-family:Courier New,monospace;font-size:8pt;color:#5a7a8a;">D2</td><td bgcolor="#141820" style="padding:6px 8px;font-family:Courier New,monospace;font-size:8pt;color:#c0392b;font-weight:bold;"><b>CRITICAL</b></td><td bgcolor="#141820" style="padding:6px 8px;font-family:Trebuchet MS,Arial,sans-serif;font-size:9pt;color:#dde6f0;">Real-time visibility into Fordow enrichment activities following IAEA monitoring disconnection.</td><td bgcolor="#141820" style="padding:6px 8px;font-family:Trebuchet MS,Arial,sans-serif;font-size:9pt;color:#5a7a8a;font-style:italic;">Without inspector access or functioning monitoring equipment, it is not possible to determine whether Iran has initiated an accelerated enrichment cycle. This gap cannot be remedied from open sources.</td></tr>

  <tr><td bgcolor="#111620" style="padding:6px 8px;font-family:Courier New,monospace;font-size:8pt;color:#00d4ff;"><b>CG-02</b></td><td bgcolor="#111620" style="padding:6px 8px;font-family:Courier New,monospace;font-size:8pt;color:#5a7a8a;">D1</td><td bgcolor="#111620" style="padding:6px 8px;font-family:Courier New,monospace;font-size:8pt;color:#d68910;font-weight:bold;"><b>SIGNIFICANT</b></td><td bgcolor="#111620" style="padding:6px 8px;font-family:Trebuchet MS,Arial,sans-serif;font-size:9pt;color:#dde6f0;">Israeli cabinet deliberations and any formal authorisation of retaliatory strikes.</td><td bgcolor="#111620" style="padding:6px 8px;font-family:Trebuchet MS,Arial,sans-serif;font-size:9pt;color:#5a7a8a;font-style:italic;">The Israeli security cabinet is meeting in restricted session. Open-source reporting captures only statements released after decisions are made.</td></tr>

  <tr><td bgcolor="#141820" style="padding:6px 8px;font-family:Courier New,monospace;font-size:8pt;color:#00d4ff;"><b>CG-03</b></td><td bgcolor="#141820" style="padding:6px 8px;font-family:Courier New,monospace;font-size:8pt;color:#5a7a8a;">D3</td><td bgcolor="#141820" style="padding:6px 8px;font-family:Courier New,monospace;font-size:8pt;color:#d68910;font-weight:bold;"><b>SIGNIFICANT</b></td><td bgcolor="#141820" style="padding:6px 8px;font-family:Trebuchet MS,Arial,sans-serif;font-size:9pt;color:#dde6f0;">Hormuz vessel traffic data disaggregated by flag state and cargo type.</td><td bgcolor="#141820" style="padding:6px 8px;font-family:Trebuchet MS,Arial,sans-serif;font-size:9pt;color:#5a7a8a;font-style:italic;">UKMTO and MarineTraffic provide incident reports but not aggregate throughput statistics in near real-time. The extent of voluntary traffic diversion versus forced rerouting is unclear.</td></tr>

  <tr><td bgcolor="#111620" style="padding:6px 8px;font-family:Courier New,monospace;font-size:8pt;color:#00d4ff;"><b>CG-04</b></td><td bgcolor="#111620" style="padding:6px 8px;font-family:Courier New,monospace;font-size:8pt;color:#5a7a8a;">D4</td><td bgcolor="#111620" style="padding:6px 8px;font-family:Courier New,monospace;font-size:8pt;color:#d68910;font-weight:bold;"><b>SIGNIFICANT</b></td><td bgcolor="#111620" style="padding:6px 8px;font-family:Trebuchet MS,Arial,sans-serif;font-size:9pt;color:#dde6f0;">Content and outcome of the Supreme National Security Council session reported on 3 March.</td><td bgcolor="#111620" style="padding:6px 8px;font-family:Trebuchet MS,Arial,sans-serif;font-size:9pt;color:#5a7a8a;font-style:italic;">The expanded SNSC session was not officially disclosed by Iran. Its agenda and any decisions taken are unknown from open sources.</td></tr>

  <tr><td bgcolor="#141820" style="padding:6px 8px;font-family:Courier New,monospace;font-size:8pt;color:#00d4ff;"><b>CG-05</b></td><td bgcolor="#141820" style="padding:6px 8px;font-family:Courier New,monospace;font-size:8pt;color:#5a7a8a;">D5</td><td bgcolor="#141820" style="padding:6px 8px;font-family:Courier New,monospace;font-size:8pt;color:#5a7a8a;font-weight:bold;"><b>MINOR</b></td><td bgcolor="#141820" style="padding:6px 8px;font-family:Trebuchet MS,Arial,sans-serif;font-size:9pt;color:#dde6f0;">Attribution confidence for GPS/AIS spoofing events in the Gulf.</td><td bgcolor="#141820" style="padding:6px 8px;font-family:Trebuchet MS,Arial,sans-serif;font-size:9pt;color:#5a7a8a;font-style:italic;">UKMTO and MarineTraffic have recorded consistent spoofing events but technical attribution to IRGC versus Houthi-aligned actors remains unclear.</td></tr>

</table>

